     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="5"/>
   <head>To Ma. Michaell Drayton.</head>
   <l>THose painfull wits, which natures depth admire,</l>
   <l>And view the causes of vnconstant strife,</l>
   <l>Doe tremble least the Vniuerse expire</l>
   <l>Through lasting iarres, the enemies of life,</l>
   <l>On earthly signes let not such Sages looke,</l>
   <l>Nor on the cleere aspects of hopefull starres,</l>
   <l>But learne the worlds continuance from thy booke,</l>
   <l>vvhich frames past Natures force eternall warres;</l>
   <l>vvherein the Muses shewing perfect glory,</l>
   <l>Adorne it so with gracefull harmonie,</l>
   <l>That all the acts of this lamented storie,</l>
   <l>Seeme not perform'd for peoples liberty.</l>
   <l>Nor through the awe of an imperious King,</l>
   <l>But that thy verses their deepe wounds might sing.</l>
   <signed>Iohn Beumont.</signed>
</div>
